            <thetext>The current trunk version of the generator has major issues when the private optimizer is enabled. When adding new private variables the optimizer seems to start again with &quot;__a&quot; ignoring that this variable is already used by another class and this way may produce overwrites in variables which leads to really crazy issues.

My early analyses seems to suggest that &quot;load()&quot; is the private optimizer is never called anymore. This was necessary IMHO to load the already applied names into memory.</thetext>
